description:
A simple PvP chess game based on inline message and edit a reply markup of a chess board. The board built with callback buttons of inline-keyboard. Bot uses the node-chess package, which is driven by the algebraic notation of moves (PGN).

To play chess simply type @chessy_bot[SPACE] to your telegram message input box. Then choose a side you want to play with. You will see an inline message with a chess board and a "Join to game" at the bottom. When someone join your game, this will be displayed in the status message. Also the "Join to game" button will become "Settings".
Now everything is ready to start the game.

The board is rotating each turn by default! The active player always placed at the bottom!
title: The PvP chess bot

description:

This bot was written on top of the Telegraf.js bot framework.

- `/start` - Initial launch of the bot.
- `/theme` - Shows the list of included themes and allows you to select a theme which you like more.
- `/langs` - Shows the list of supported languages.
